13/04/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- As expected, representatives from Bulgaria, Greece and Russia sealed the long-awaited political accords for a major regional oil pipeline Tuesday (12 April) in Sofia. The 300km pipeline, which will cost around $700m, is expected to carry Caspian crude oil from the Bulgarian port of Bourgas to Alexandroupolis in Greece. (bTV, ANA, MPA - 12/04/05) 
